You are now correlating requests across services, traces, and queues. The final step is making those logs truly queryable. That is where Serilog shines: every event is structured, property names are consistent, and correlation becomes a first-class field instead of a string hidden in message text.

This part shows a Serilog-first implementation for the same maintenance platform used across the series.

